    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Creates a new pool for the given token pair and fee tier.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n* `e` - The contract environment\\n* `token_a` - First token address\\n* `token_b` - Second token address\\n* `fee` - Fee tier in basis points\\n\\n# Returns\\n* `Ok(Address)` - Address of the newly created pool\\n* `Err(Error)` - If validation fails (see pool::create_pool for error codes)",
      "name": "create_pool",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_a",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_b",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fee",
          "type_": "u32"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "result": {
            "ok_type": "address",
            "error_type": "error"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "function_v0": {
      "doc": "Creates a pool if it doesn't exist and initializes it atomically.\\n\\nThis mirrors Uniswap V3's `createAndInitializePoolIfNecessary` behavior:\\n- If the pool for `(tokenA, tokenB, fee)` does not exist, it is deployed via the factory.\\n- The pool's `initialize(sqrt_price_x96)` is then invoked in the same Soroban call.\\n\\nThe entire operation is atomic: if initialization fails (e.g., invalid price or pool\\nalready initialized), the transaction reverts and the pool creation is rolled back.\\n\\n# Arguments\\n* `e` - The contract environment\\n* `token_a` - First token address\\n* `token_b` - Second token address\\n* `fee` - Fee tier in basis points\\n* `sqrt_price_x96` - Initial sqrt price in Q64.96 format\\n\\n# Returns\\n* `Ok(Address)` - Address of the pool (created or existing)\\n* `Err(Error)` - If creation or initialization fails\\n\\n# Notes\\n- If the pool already exists and is initialized, this call no-ops and returns the address.\\n- If the pool already exists but is not initialized, it will be initialized.",
      "name": "create_and_initialize_pool",
      "inputs": [
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_a",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "token_b",
          "type_": "address"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "fee",
          "type_": "u32"
        },
        {
          "doc": "",
          "name": "sqrt_price_x96",
          "type_": "u256"
        }
      ],
      "outputs": [
        {
          "result": {
            "ok_type": "address",
            "error_type": "error"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
